{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4315a83c-0b78-44d5-b87c-4f3438dc42f6","content":"Here's the mapping from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/*/*/*[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Flag-by-flag translation:**\n\n| VSTest (old) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform (new) |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/*/*/*[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Everything after `--` is forwarded to the test host.\n- The treenode filter uses a path syntax (`/assembly/namespace/class[trait=value]`); `/*/*/*` wildcards match any assembly/namespace/class.\n- If your tests use `[TestCategory(\"Integration\")]` (MSTest), use `TestCategory` instead of `Category` in the filter.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c22abaf0-a7f5-42b1-9562-fc92f911346b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I can answer this directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me break down each flag and its Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalent:\n\n1. `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` → `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` (same syntax works)\n2. `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` \n3. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` or use `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage\n\n\n4. `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n5. `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n6. `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nThe key thing to remember is that while `dotnet test` still works as a wrapper around Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the underlying flag names have changed. Some flags like `--filter` remain the same, but others like the blame-related flags have been renamed to be more explicit about what they do.\n\nFor .NET 8 specifically with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to clarify whether the user is running the test executable directly or going through `dotnet test`, since that affects how arguments get passed through. The filter syntax differs between VSTest and Microsoft.Testing.Platform, but when using `dotnet test` as the entry point, the `--filter` flag should still work and get translated appropriately. The most practical approach is to place the filter before the `--` separator, then pass the other options after it. Completing the flag mappings table... Passing the tree node filter and other options through the `--` separator to the test host. I should also mention the required NuGet packages for features like trx reporting and coverage output.","outputTokens":2275,"requestId":"981F:FCC6:178372:1EEADD:69FFD875"},"id":"fa9b5040-a744-4f2b-b834-3398282ce8b7","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:00:10.074Z","parentId":"f2686cc4-ef0a-47e5-8a56-f3a8fae4fb47"}
